<p>One of the fun things about late 80s/early 90s games is seeing all the weird ways they tried "fake 3D." This is Narco Police (1989). Instead of scaling, they just scroll the walls down. It's iffy, but it's smoother/higher fidelity than scaling and prolly saves space + compute.</p>
